    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Dregea abyssinica improperly are experience nausea, cause diarrhea, experience dizziness, induce nausea, and vomiting, which are primarily due to its emetic properties. This is because the plant contains alkaloids that stimulate the vomiting center in the brain, leading to these adverse reactions. The improper use of Dregea abyssinica can also cause gastrointestinal irritation, resulting in abdominal cramps, and potentially lead to dehydration due to excessive fluid loss. Furthermore, the emetic effects can be unpredictable and may vary in severity depending on the individual's sensitivity and the method of administration. It is essential to use Dregea abyssinica under the guidance of a qualified healthcare professional to minimize the risk of these side effects.",
